## Steps

### step 1
id: navigate-to-payer-directory
instruction: Click "Payer Directory" in the main sidebar.
success_criteria: You are on the Payer Directory page showing a table of payers with columns for Name, EDI Payer ID, Coverage, and States.
anchor: payer-directory-nav-link
on_success: next
on_stuck: The Payer Directory link is in the left sidebar. It is separate from Payer Intelligence — the directory shows identifying information like EDI IDs, while Payer Intel shows billing policies.

### step 2
id: search-for-payer
instruction: Type the payer's name (or part of it) in the search bar to filter the list. You can also use the coverage type or state filters to narrow results further.
success_criteria: The payer you are looking for is visible in the filtered table.
anchor: payer-directory-search-bar
on_success: next
on_stuck: Try searching by a shorter part of the name, or try an alternate name (e.g., "BCBS" instead of "Blue Cross Blue Shield"). The directory includes "Also Known As" entries for payers with multiple names.

### step 3
id: expand-payer-row
instruction: Click on the payer's row in the table to expand it and view the full details panel.
success_criteria: The expanded panel is visible showing clearinghouse IDs, all operating states, alternative payer names (Also Known As), and a link to the payer's website.
anchor: payer-row
on_success: next
on_stuck: Click anywhere on the payer row to expand it. The panel appears inline below the row — scroll down if needed.

### step 4
id: copy-edi-payer-id
instruction: Note the EDI Payer ID from the row or the expanded panel. This is the ID you need when setting up claims routing or verifying payer registration.
success_criteria: You have the correct EDI Payer ID for the payer. If you need clearinghouse-specific IDs, those are also shown in the expanded panel.
anchor: edi-payer-id
on_success: completion
on_stuck: The EDI Payer ID appears in the table row. Expand the row for clearinghouse-specific IDs if your practice uses multiple clearinghouses.

## Completion Message
payer found! use the EDI Payer ID when submitting claims or setting up payer routing. if the payer you need isn't in the directory, check the Unresolved tab — it lists payers that have appeared on your claims but haven't been matched yet.

